body.prompt:
Generate a fake conversation between a customer and an agent.
The agent should introduce themselves, their company and give the customer
their name. The agent should ask for the customer's name.
As part of the conversation, have the agent ask for two pieces of
personal information.  Spell out numbers. For example, 1000 should be
said as one zero zero zero, not one thousand. The conversation should be
at least 10 lines long and be complete. At the end
of the conversation, the agent should thank the customer for their time
and end the conversation. Return the conversation formatted 
like the following example:

{'conversation': 
    [
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': 'xxxxx'}, 
    {'speaker': 'Customer', 'message': "xxxxx."}, 
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': "xxxxxx"}
    ] 
}

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Hello, thank you for contacting CarMart Customer Support. My name is Kevin Washington.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: May I please have your name?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Hello, my name is Teresa Gonzales.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Nice to meet you, Teresa. How can I assist you today?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: I had recently returned a vehicle and I have not received my refund yet.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: I'm sorry to hear that. Can you please provide me with the return tracking number and the date you returned the vehicle?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: The tracking number is one four five six two and I returned the vehicle on the twenty-second of September.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you for providing that information, Teresa. I will look into this for you.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you for your patience, Teresa. We have located the refund and it will be processed within 3-5 business days.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you for reaching out to us. Have a great day, Teresa.

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Thank you for your help. Goodbye.
